CWebSocketServerForFlutterPanel — License and Notices

Copyright 2025 kozakemi

This project is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see `LICENSE` at the repository root). This NOTICE file is provided to satisfy the acknowledgment and license notice obligations under Apache 2.0 Section 4(d), and to summarize third‑party dependencies and compliance notes.

Third‑Party Dependencies and Licenses:
- libwebsockets — License: LGPL‑2.1.
  - Note: The project dynamically links the system‑provided `libwebsockets` via the compiler/linker flag `-lwebsockets`.
  - Compliance: Dynamic linking generally preserves the user’s right to use a modified version of the library (by replacing the runtime shared object). Keep the library’s license and copyright notices, and comply with LGPL‑2.1.
  - Reference: Distribution license documents (e.g., Debian `/usr/share/doc/libwebsockets-dev/copyright`) or https://libwebsockets.org/.

- cJSON — License: MIT.
  - Note: Source code is included in `lib/cJSON/`; keep its `LICENSE` file and the MIT license headers in source files.
  - Reference: `lib/cJSON/LICENSE`, https://github.com/DaveGamble/cJSON.

- wpa_supplicant (used via the `wpa_cli` command‑line tool) — License: GPLv2.
  - Note: This project does not distribute `wpa_supplicant`; it is used as a runtime dependency provided by the system. Follow the distribution license terms from the system provider.
  - Reference: https://w1.fi/wpa_supplicant/.

Distribution and Compliance Tips:
- Project source and binaries are distributed under Apache‑2.0; retain this NOTICE and third‑party license files in distributions.
- For `libwebsockets` compliance:
  - If dynamically linked (current default): Users may replace the runtime shared library to use their modified version; do not employ technical measures that prevent reverse engineering or library replacement for relinking.
  - If statically linked: Provide relinkable object files (e.g., `.o`) or an equivalent mechanism to enable relinking against a modified library, satisfying LGPL obligations.

Examples of using a modified `libwebsockets` (for illustration only):
- Install a custom `libwebsockets.so` to `/usr/local/lib` and run `ldconfig`, or set `LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/lib` prior to launching the program to override the system library search path.
- At runtime, the program will load the custom shared library, effectively relinking to the modified version.

This file is a compliance summary and does not replace the full license texts. Please read and follow the complete licenses when distributing or using this software.